event.title: Hong Kong HOS Application
event.description:
1. Submission: Fill and submit one-form-three-draw application online/written (ID, income proof, asset declaration).
2. Processing: Enter lottery draw for building selection order <Time: 1-2 weeks>.
3. Selection: Attend selection center to choose unit and sign provisional agreement <Time: 1-2 months>.
4. Activation: Complete mortgage, pay deposit, and move in upon completion.

event.title: Hong Kong HOS Application (Red Tape)
event.description:
1. Prerequisite Hurdle: Verify no property ownership in past 24 months via Lands Department check. <Barrier: Historical Records Verification> <Cost: At least 1 week for certificate issuance>
2. The Proof Hunt: Obtain stamped income/asset proofs from employer/bank. <Barrier: Multi-Source Documentation> <Action: Appointments at banks> <Cost: 1 full day collecting>
3. Submission: Submit application online/written.
4. Information Black Hole: Wait for lottery results with limited updates. <Barrier: Lack of Transparency> <Cost: High Anxiety>
5. Forced Inquiry: Call/Visit Housing Authority for eligibility confirmation. <Action: Active Chasing> <Cost: More Effort/Transport>
6. The Salami Slicing Request: Receive request for additional family proofs (e.g., marriage cert not listed). <Barrier: Hidden Rule/Vague Requirement> <Cost: Wait another 1-2 weeks>
7. Approval: Win lottery and get invitation.
8. Mainland Delay: For cross-border families, extra certification from Home Affairs. <Barrier: Inter-Department Coordination> <Cost: 3-7 workdays>
9. Activation: Sign and pay, but mortgage approval delayed by bank stress test waiver issues.
